## 4 Experiments

In this section, both synthetic and real-world experiments are conducted to evaluate the prediction accuracy and fairness of our approach. The root mean squared error (RMSE) between \(Y\) and \(\hat{Y}\) is used to measure the prediction performance, and the RMSE between \(\hat{Y}|do(A=a)\) and \(\hat{Y}|do(A=a^{\prime})\) is used to measure the violation of the interventional fairness, named "unfairness".

